The paper deals with image analysis and classification, specifically for age and gender classification from ear images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves the use of deep convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the technology in human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the study involves the use of a large-scale dataset and domain adaptation techniques, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR).
